Yeah something similar to Gateway/Snowglobe/Funding.

We deploy two days a week. We cut a version tag. That version tag has a release notes page that breaks down all of the changes in that release. Telemetry gets tagged with a version rather than a commit sha. When debugging a problem, the engineer knows where to find all the commits that belong to a version tag.

An example of where this can break down now:

* A new exception pops up in Sentry
* Sentry shows that it's tied to a particular commit
* You look up the commit and see nothing in the change set related to the error
* You then have to go back and figure out if commits before this commit were deployed independently or if they were bundled with the tagged commit's changes
