A lot of the friction is coming from folks not filling out the workflow, filling the workflow out on top of each other, and overall losing track of what has/has not been deployed after factoring in the workflow time delay (as well as the dev who filled out the workflow not actually having prod access to take their changes out themselves).

Having a clearer process/schedule for when devs can expect their changes to go out and need to be validated would be better in this new way of working IMO (edited) 

